verbose_text: Most important risk factors for osteoporosis are : age, female sex, ethnic group, genetic factors, inherited factors, early menopause, slim silhouette and low body mass, diseases disturbing the bone metabolism, some medicines taken for a long time, insufficient physical activity, consumption of too small amounts of calcium and vitamin D, overconsumption of alcohol, caffeine and cigarette smoking and protein rich diet [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: amounts of calcium and vitamin D
